Xiao was holding on to.

232
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:21,510
He wasn't innocent.

233
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,350
He wasn't worth pitying.

234
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:26,980
All I did was use a piece of tape

235
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,850
to transfer his fingerprints
from his glass

236
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:29,790
onto the knife.

237
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:31,630
I didn't expect

238
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,060
you'd trace it back to him.

239
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:37,700
Do you regret it?

240
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:39,580
Regret?

241
00:15:44,190 --> 00:15:45,910
The only thing I regret

242
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:47,980
is letting that scumbag, Liu Ang,

243
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:49,310
die too easily!

244
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,830
Then let me tell you something.

245
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:53,990
When our forensic team

246
00:15:54,510 --> 00:15:55,940
was examining Liu Ang's body,

247
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:57,990
they discovered that he had late-stage

248
00:15:58,430 --> 00:15:59,260
liver cancer.

249
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:00,350
And you

250
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:02,300
gave him a painless death.

251
00:16:04,540 --> 00:16:05,070
What?

252
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:08,740
He had cancer?

253
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:11,390
No...

254
00:16:13,350 --> 00:16:13,940
Impossible!

255
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:15,300
You're lying!

256
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:26,460
I don't regret it.

257
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:28,350
I don't regret it!

258
00:16:29,070 --> 00:16:30,740
No, I don't!

259
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:41,830
Xiao suffered

260
