00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,430
a crime?

295
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:45,150
Xu Dongyang,

296
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:47,780
we wouldn't be arresting you

297
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:48,910
without solid evidence.

298
00:18:49,590 --> 00:18:51,390
If you refuse to confess,

299
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:53,540
you're only making things worse
for yourself.

300
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:55,350
The person who can help you now

301
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:56,780
is yourself.

302
00:20:28,350 --> 00:20:29,590
We also found a sofa.

303
00:20:30,430 --> 00:20:33,260
Its style, color, and size match

304
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:35,350
the ones from your living room.

305
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:38,540
Under one of the cushions,

306
00:20:39,150 --> 00:20:40,190
we found your hair

307
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:42,500
and half of Tang Xinxin's fingernail.

308
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:44,910
How do you explain?

309
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,780
The sofa got dirty.

310
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:57,850
So I threw it out.

311
00:20:58,630 --> 00:21:00,260
If someone else killed her on it,

312
00:21:01,070 --> 00:21:02,190
that's not my problem, right?

313
00:21:03,460 --> 00:21:05,980
Tang Xinxin and I fought before.

314
00:21:05,980 --> 00:21:06,700
Maybe

315
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:08,910
she lost the nail back then.

316
00:21:08,910 --> 00:21:09,830
That's possible, right?

317
00:21:10,910 --> 00:21:11,430
You have

318
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:13,260
severe OCD
and a major cleanliness obsession.

319
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:15,540
There's no way
you'd keep something in your house

320
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:16,460
if someone died on it.

321
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:18,300
So you got rid of it

322
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:19,110
as fast as you could.

323
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:21,590
But what you didn't expect

324
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:23,910
was that Tang Xinxin left behind

325
00:21:23,910 --> 00:21:25,460
something very important.

326
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:38,110
Why make me take
the clothes home today?

327
00:21:39,670 --> 00:21:40,500
I have a date.

328
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,460
Why make me take
the clothes home today?

329
00:21:48,630 --> 00:21:49,670
I have a date.

330
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:00,830
Who are you drinking with?

331
00:22:01,670 --> 00:22:03,150
Found yourself a new guy already?

332
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:04,910
Answer me.

333
00:22:05,870 --> 00:22:07,740
Did you take the money

334
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:09,670
I left for my dad?

335
00:22:09,830 --> 00:22:10,740
You were the one

336
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:12,950
who promised me two million yuan
for emotional damages.

337
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:13,700
Where's the money?

338
00:22:14,150 --> 00:22:14,780
I want my money.

339
00:22:15,190 --> 00:22:16,870
I only took 500,000 yuan.

340
00:22:16,870 --> 00:22:18,260
You still owe me 1.5 million yuan.

341
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:20,590
That was the money I set aside
for my dad's retirement!

342
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:21,870
Tang Xinxin,

343
00:22:22,390 --> 00:22:24,630
you must not cross the line.

344
00:22:25,390 --> 00:22:27,700
I found out you were married before
and had a kid.

345
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:29,740
You were trying
to scam me into marriage.

346
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:31,070
You lied to me,

347
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:33,980
saying you were single, unmarried,
and even pretended to be a virgin.

348
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:35,700
You should be the one paying me!

349
00:22:35,980 --> 00:22:37,870
So what if I was married and had a kid?

350
00:22:38,110 --> 00:22:39,630
Have you looked in the mirror?

351
00:22:39,630 --> 00:22:41,150
With so many handsome guys out there,

352
00:22:41,630 --> 00:22:42,700
you think I would pick you?

353
00:22:43,020 --> 00:22:44,500
You're pathetic!

354
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:46,980
I bought you plenty of things, didn't I?

355
00:22:47,390 --> 00:22:48,630
You are so greedy.

356
00:22:48,630 --> 00:22:50,070
I deserve those things.

357
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:51,500
I don't care.

358
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:53,070
You still owe me 1.5 million.

359
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:54,780
If you don't pay up,

360
00:22:54,780 --> 00:22:56,870
I'll report you for tax evasion

361
00:22:57,070 --> 00:22:58,150
and embezzlement.

362
00:22:58,260 --> 00:23:00,540
If it weren't for you forcing me
to buy luxury goods

363
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:01,350
and a villa,

364
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:02,990
I wouldn't have had to do any of that!

365
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:06,350
You were the one who did those things.

366
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:07,540
Don't drag me into it.

367
00:23:07,870 --> 00:23:09,350
If I had known you were so useless,

368
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:10,430
I would not have wasted

369
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,670
so much time on you.

370
00:23:11,870 --> 00:23:13,150
You're short and have no looks.

371
00:23:13,150 --> 00:23:14,740
You even want to be an entrepreneur

372
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,400
and drag me down with your misfortunes?

373
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,700
Do you have to be so heartless?

374
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,870
I don't care.

375
00:23:19,870 --> 00:23:20,780
You have one week

376
00:23:21,190 --> 00:23:22,460
to transfer another 500,000 yuan.

377
00:23:22,460 --> 00:23:23,910
If the money is not in my account,

378
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:25,260
I'll expose your deeds online!

379
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,070
What's wrong with you?

380
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:33,460
What are you doing?

381
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,190
Let me go, Xu Dongyang!

382
00:23:35,190 --> 00:23:36,460
Get off me!

383
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:38,500
Help! Help!

384
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,350
You want money, huh?

385
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:05,630
Here's your money!

386
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:07,260
You wretched woman,

387
00:24:07,870 --> 00:24:09,300
you can die with it!

388
00:24:12,780 --> 00:24:13,670
You want money, huh?

389
00:24:13,980 --> 00:24:14,870
Here's your money!

390
00:24:15,430 --> 00:24:16,630
You wretched woman,

391
00:24:17,150 --> 00:24:18,590
you can die with it!

392
00:24:34,670 --> 00:24:35,630
You have no idea

393
00:24:36,740 --> 00:24:38,300
how greedy

394
00:24:38,830 --> 00:24:39,940
Tang Xinxin was.

395
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:43,430
You don't know

396
00:24:44,020 --> 00:24:44,830
how hard I worked

397
00:24:44,830 --> 00:24:45,870
to build "She, He, and It".

398
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:50,260
"She, He, and It"

399
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:53,020
had drained my creativity.

400
00:24:55,780 --> 00:24:56,670
And Tang Xinxin

401
00:24:58,350 --> 00:25:00,390
stole everything
that I've accomplished from me!

402
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:01,940
I only wanted

403
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:04,020
to get rid

404
00:25:04,590 --> 00:25:05,670
of that filthy sofa

405
00:25:06,220 --> 00:25:07,700
as soon as possible

406
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:10,190
and punish

407
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:12,740
that woman

408
00:25:13,940 --> 00:25:15,630
in my own way.

409
00:25:17,460 --> 00:25:18,590
(I grew up poor.)

410
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,740
(I worked hard to get into university.)

411
00:25:21,230 --> 00:25:23,550
(I worked part-time jobs
to pay my way through university.)

412
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,550
(I even gave up my spot
for postgraduate studies)

413
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:27,260
(to start making money faster.)

414
00:25:30,260 --> 00:25:31,670
(No company wanted to hire me.)

415
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,170
(I had to deliver packages
during the day)

416
00:25:34,870 --> 00:25:36,190
(and code at night.)

417
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,260
(I created over a dozen mini-programs)

418
00:25:39,390 --> 00:25:40,490
(but none of them took off.)

419
00:25:41,430 --> 00:25:43,350
(It wasn't until I launched
"She, He, and It".)

420
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:44,830
(Do you know)

421
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:47,430
(how much effort it took)

422
00:25:47,830 --> 00:25:49,780
(to go from 100 downloads to a million?)

423
00:25:50,350 --> 00:25:51,350
(Fixing bugs)

424
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:53,870
(and dealing with massive amounts
of data every day.)

425
00:25:53,870 --> 00:25:54,870
(Back-end Monitoring Data)

426
00:25:54,870 --> 00:25:57,500
(Then investors finally
started noticing me.)

427
00:25:58,430 --> 00:26:00,590
(I thought my big break had come.)

428
00:26:00,910 --> 00:26:01,940
(That was)

429
00:26:02,540 --> 00:26:03,630
(when I met her.)

430
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:05,740
I never cared about looks

431
00:26:05,740 --> 00:26:06,870
or family background.

432
00:26:07,350 --> 00:26:09,220
I only want to find an honest
and reliable man

433
00:26:09,220 --> 00:26:09,950
who treat me well,

434
00:26:10,390 --> 00:26:11,070
listen to me,

435
00:26:11,430 --> 00:26:13,110
and truly want to get married.

436
00:26:13,620 --> 00:26:14,780
I promise I'll be good to you.

437
00:26:14,780 --> 00:26:16,120
I'll listen to you no matter what.

438
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:18,390
I think men should have dreams too.

439
00:26:18,830 --> 00:26:20,590
You don't have to sacrifice anything
for me.

440
00:26:21,110 --> 00:26:22,870
I want to be the woman
behind your success.

441
00:26:23,070 --> 00:26:23,700
You're so nice.

442
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:28,940
(I didn't have any experience
in dating.)

443
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:30,630
(She was my first love.)

444
00:26:30,820 --> 00:26:31,940
(I did everything she asked.)

445
00:26:31,940 --> 00:26:33,070
Is this dress pretty?

446
00:26:33,070 --> 00:26:33,980
(I gave her everything)

447
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:34,740
(she wanted.)

448
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:35,350
It looks great.

449
00:26:35,590 --> 00:26:36,260
(But then)

450
00:26:36,260 --> 00:26:36,870
It's pretty.

451
00:26:37,020 --> 00:26:38,590
(her demands kept growing)

452
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:39,830
(and were more costly.)

453
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,690
(When I couldn't afford them,)

454
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,630
(she started making a fuss.)

